ENTRY       EC 3.5.5.5                  Enzyme
NAME        arylacetonitrilase
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on carbon-nitrogen bonds, other than peptide bonds;
            In nitriles
SYSNAME     arylacetonitrile aminohydrolase
REACTION    4-chlorophenylacetonitrile + 2 H2O = 4-chlorophenylacetate + NH3 [RN:R04140]
ALL_REAC    R04140;
            (other) R00540
SUBSTRATE   4-chlorophenylacetonitrile [CPD:C03679];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     4-chlorophenylacetate [CPD:C03077];
            NH3 [CPD:C00014]
COMMENT     Requires thiol compounds. Also hydrolyses other 4-substituted phenylacetonitriles, thien-2-ylacetonitrile, tolylacetonitriles, and, more slowly, benzyl cyanide.
